name: ContextSymbols
description:
Creates a proxy which provides us access to the symbols
defined in given context (could be lazy loaded module or the root module).

name: constructor
description: Creates an instance of ContextSymbols.

name: getModules
description: Returns the metadata associated to this module.

name: getDirectives
description: Returns all the directives available in the context.

name: getPipes
description: Returns all the pipes available in this module.

name: getContextSummary
description: Returns the summary of this context.

name: updateProgram
description:
Updates the program which has impact over the loaded symbols.
In case the `udpate` method is called with program different from
the current one, all the internal caches will be cleared.

name: getDirectiveFromNode
description: Returns directive based on `ClassDeclaration` node and a filename.

name: DirectiveSymbol
description:
This class represents the individual directives and wrapps
their `StaticSymbol`s produced by the `@angular/compiler`.

name: constructor
description: Creates an instance of DirectiveSymbol.

name: getNonResolvedMetadata
description:
Returns the non-resolved metadata for given directive.
If it is a component, this means that the external templates
and styles won't be read from the drive. Also, the paths to
external metadata won't be resolved.

name: getResolvedMetadata
description:
Returns the normalized and resolved metadata for given directive or component.
For components, all the external templates and styles will be read and
set as values of the returned `CompileTemplateMetadata` properties.

name: getModule
description: Returns the module where the given directive has been declared.

name: getStyleAsts
description: Returns the ASTs of all styles of the target directive.

name: getDirectiveContext
description:
Returns the context into which the template of given
component is going to be compiled.

name: getTemplateAst
description: Returns the compiled template of the target component.

name: isComponent
description: Returns if the target directive is a component.

name: getModuleSummary
description: Returns the summary of this context.

name: PipeSymbol
description: A wrapper around the pipe symbol.

name: constructor
description: Creates an instance of PipeSymbol.

name: getModule
description: Returns the module where the wrapped pipe was defined.

name: getMetadata
description: Returns the pipe metadata.

name: ProjectSymbols
description:
Creates a proxy which provides us access to the symbols
defined in given context (could be lazy loaded module or the root module).

name: constructor
description: Creates an instance of ProjectSymbols.

name: getModules
description: Returns the metadata associated to this module.

name: getDirectives
description: Returns all the directives available in the context.

name: getPipes
description: Returns all the pipes available in this module.

name: getProviders
description: Returns all the providers available in this module.

name: updateProgram
description:
Updates the program which has impact over the loaded symbols.
In case the `update` method is called with program different from
the current one, all the internal caches will be cleared.

name: getDirectiveFromNode
description: Returns directive based on `ClassDeclaration` node and a filename.

name: getMetadata
description: Returns the provider metadata.

name: getDependencies
description: Returns the list of dependencies for given provider.

name: Symbol
description:
Base class which provides primitive for the DirectiveSymbol and
PipeSymbol. It contains some functionality common between these classes.

name: constructor
description: Creates an instance of Symbol.

name: getNode
description:
Gets the ts.node which corresponds to the controller of the DirectiveSymbol
or the implementation of the pipe.

name: symbol
description: The wrapped `StaticSymbol` from `@angular/compiler`.
